  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Slice the <strong>cauliflower<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> steaks, approx. 3cm thick (use the middle part as it's larger!), reserve the<strong> remaining cauliflower</strong> and discard the leaves</p><p>Deseed the <strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon), cut into large chunks then crush the <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife, discard the skins</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684422208929-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684422208929-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684422208929-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684422208929-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1684422208929-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cauliflower steaks</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the cauliflower to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray (or two!) with the <strong>chopped pepper</strong>,<strong> peeled garlic </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Make 2 separate parcels!</p><p>Put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for 15-20 min or until the pepper is slightly charred</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684422213201-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1684422213201-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
